Reasoning: The paper discusses an empirical study of algorithms for syntactic centric aspect-based opinion mining, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The study also involves parameter setting and implementation details, which are important components of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The use of algorithms for opinion mining also relates to information retrieval (cs.IR) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
